[November 2011] ==============================================================

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scidb 1.0 BETA (rev. #132)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Elo added in game info of PGN editor.

* Problem with hard links solved. It is not allowed to open a database twice
- the application may crash - and to open an already loaded database will be
denied. To accomplish this the detection of hard links is required.

* Bug in browser and overview related to game loading fixed.

* Hopefully a problem with initialization order of static objects solved.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scidb 1.0 BETA (rev. #131)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* libharu: upgraded to version 2.3 (libharu.org).

* libharu: HPDF_GetTTFontDef() implemented.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scidb 1.0 BETA (rev. #130)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Upgrading of databases tweaked.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scidb 1.0 BETA (rev. #129)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Some tweaks in file selection box.

* Bug with opening of read-only databases fixed.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scidb 1.0 BETA (rev. #128)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Severe bug in save/replace dialog fixed. This bug is related to the speed up
changes in rev. #96.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scidb 1.0 BETA (rev. #127)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Some bugs related to charset detection fixed.

* Bug in file selection box fixed.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scidb 1.0 BETA (rev. #126)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* cbh2si4 tweaked.

* Some bugs related to charset detection fixed.

* Severe bug in si3 encoding fixed.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scidb 1.0 BETA (rev. #103)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Photo files (.spf, .spi, .spa) eliminated, now every photo is a single file.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scidb 1.0 BETA (rev. #102)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Crash immediately after startup fixed, which occurred only on some systems.

* cbh2si4 improved. The user may optionally determine the exported tags,
because this affects position search time (size of the game file).

* Sub-project universalchardet added (character set detector from
Mozilla/Firefox).

* Load database: auto-detection of character set implemented.

* Import PGN game: auto-detection of character set implemented.
* Import PGN game: auto-detection of figurine set implemented.

[October 2011] ===============================================================

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scidb 1.0 BETA (rev. #101)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Bug with re-opening the file selection box fixed.

* Bug in namebase fixed (error case: encoding of .si4 namebase fails, which
may result in id's higher than the number of entries).

* Function forceValidUtf8() fixed.

* Problem in configure script fixed.

[September/October 2011] =====================================================

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scidb 1.0 BETA (rev. #96)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Severe bug in block file buffer fixed. This means that storing of games in
databases should work now.

* Second speed improvement of the Html widget: double buffering implemented.
But this feature needs testing.

* Third improvement of the Html widget: memory allocator implemented in
libTeXt.

* Game history implemented.

* Reading CBH database fixed (problem with namebases).

* Correction of character encoding handling.

* Correction of PGN view box ("see" method).

* Implementation of modernized menues finished. Probably this feature will
be optionally usable in a later version.

* Severe bug in position tree building fixed (Chess 960 search algorithm
reimplemented).  This fix has required a change of the .sci database format
(index data only). Ths version of the database format has increased to 0.92.
The database upgrade at opening time of the database is enabled (but an
upgrade is not mandatory although the old format is causing errors).

* Problem with castling in FRC positions fixed.

* Problem with generation of castling moves in internal engine fixed.

* Undo/redo problems in PGN editor fixed.

* Additional ports needed to locate the architecture dependent libX11.so libs
added to configure script.

* Animation of castling moves fixed.

* Current game now will be highlighted if in trial mode.

* Storing/retrieving move information (analysis information, players clock,
elapsed game/move time, time information, evaluation information, etc...)
is prepared. This change requires an update of the Scidb database.

* Speed up of save/replace dialog (popup time).

* Magic file corrected, will now show a string like "Scidb index, version
0.92, 14820 game(s)"

* Bug in configure script fixed: "./configure --tcl-version=8.6" should work
now.

* Tournament table enhanced: new version includes additional tie-breaks
"Games won with Black", "Particular Result", "Traditional Scoring"; new
scoring system "Bilbao" (three points for a win).

* Export to .si3/si4: Additional tab for selection of the exported tags. This
is necessary to limit the database size, which affects the search time of the
opening tree.

* Problem with game loading fixed.

* Bug in annotation window fixed; all buttons will be disabled if no game is
open.

* Formating error in PGN window fixed (db_edit_node.cpp:pushParagraph()).

* Change database icon dialog improved.

* Comment editor improved.

* New function in PGN editor: copy/move comments from one language code to
another language code.

[August 2011] ================================================================

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scidb 1.0 BETA (rev. #94)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Severe error with marks in si3::Consumer and si3::Encoder fixed.

* Severe errors in overview.tcl and browser.tcl fixed.

* On Fedora systems the truetype fonts will be installed in /usr (not
/usr/local).

* Database upgrade implemented (not yet used).

* Focus problem in tree game list solved.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scidb 1.0 BETA (rev. #92)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Bug item #3381510 fixed.
* Bug item #3381580 fixed.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scidb 1.0 BETA (rev. #91)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* m_types.h updated: g++ versions < 4.6 are not really ready for C++0x
standard (previous patch failed).

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scidb 1.0 BETA (rev. #90)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* m_types.h updated: g++ versions < 4.6 are not really ready for C++0x
standard.

[July 2011] ==================================================================

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scidb 1.0 BETA (rev. #89)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* First speed improvement of the Html widget (highlighting). The slowness
seems to be a general problem if a large window is involved, but this needs
further investigation.

* Comment parsing and tokenizing fixed.

* Update problem with game header fixed.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scidb 1.0 BETA (rev. #87)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Event info popup implemented (ButtonPress-2).

* Problem with fullscreen mode fixed (bug item #3369168).

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scidb 1.0 BETA (rev. #86)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Upgrade to C++0x standard.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scidb 1.0 BETA (rev. #81)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Invalid date entries in .si3/4 bases will be refused now.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scidb 1.0 BETA (rev. #80)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Busy cursor stuff reimplemention refined.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scidb 1.0 BETA (rev. #79)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Busy cursor stuff reimplemented.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scidb 1.0 BETA (rev. #77)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Bug with bottom space underneath board (hopefully) fixed (bug item #3349601)

* Engines added (MicroMax and TogaII-1.3.1).

* tkmenu.tcl changed: modernized menu behavior, but only available under
windoze (modernized does not mean "better").

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scidb 1.0 BETA (rev. #76)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* configure script changed, hopefully it will now detect versions >= 4.5 of
the gnu compiler.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scidb 1.0 BETA (rev. #71)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Correction of variation folding: a folded variation does not show comments
anymore.

* Eco translation from Fernando integrated. Both translation now are macRoman
encoded.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scidb 1.0 BETA (rev. #70)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* startHtmlElement() fixed (game recovery should be correct now).

* Game header of recovered games ok now.

* Problem with black castling on main board fixed (bug item #3356896).

* The configure script will now add -fno-stack-protector option if supported;
Ubuntu 11.04 has stack protection on per default, but I dont want this; makes
the program slower and is satisfying only the paranoid people.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scidb 1.0 BETA (rev. #69)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Game list: Shift-Double-Button-1 will switch to the board tab after loading
the game (see feature request #3349617).

* web::open reimplemented, see bug item #3349635.

* Scidb is now remembering the icon size (already fixed in rev. #68).

* PGN reader will warn about failed encoding only once.

* Encoding problems with PGN files fixed (default encoding is ISO8859-1).

* Checksum computation fixed: the game bar should not load anymore an already
open game.

* <Shift-Double-Button-1> bound to game list on database tab: switch to the
main board when loading a game.
